main event: Unidentified flying objects were observed by military and civilian personnel in Cheyenne, Wyoming on September 3, 1965 and September 8, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were described as bright, white in color, and moving in various directions, hovering, then accelerating rapidly.
The objects were tracked by a Geodetic Survey Team, who considered them unusual and unable to identify.

On September 8, 1965, a large, elliptical-shaped object with red and green lights around the circumference was observed hovering for several minutes before accelerating and climbing rapidly out of sight.
Radar tracked the object and lost it, and the sighting was confirmed by the control tower.

The objects were observed through binoculars and described as circular or disc-shaped, with a slight concentration of light or glow in the center and a gray color, moving at a rapid rate and changing course.
sighted object: bright, white objects; large, elliptical-shaped object with red and green lights; circular or disc-shaped objects
